{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/subscriptions/openaisub","identifier":"RefreshDefaultProviderSubscription","question":"What kinds of errors can RefreshDefaultProviderSubscription return, and should CLI startup validation treat those errors as fatal even when other LLM auth is configured?","answer":"`RefreshDefaultProviderSubscription` is best-effort startup sync for the default OpenAI subscription auth file.\n\nDocumented behavior:\n- It “refreshes and syncs default saved auth for startup availability.”\n- Startup paths explicitly refresh expired default saved auth “when possible.”\n- Missing saved auth is not an error.\n- Usable auth registers an OpenAI provider subscription with `llmmodel`; unusable auth clears it.\n\nImplementation facts:\n- Returns `nil` when the default auth file is missing.\n- Returns `nil` when auth is expired but refresh is impossible or fails, including HTTP/network/401/timeout/invalid refresh response errors. In that case it syncs the old auth, which usually clears the OpenAI subscription because it is not valid.\n- Can return errors from local auth file handling:\n  - read errors other than `os.ErrNotExist`\n  - JSON parse errors, wrapped as `read OpenAI subscription auth: ...`\n  - save errors after a successful refresh, such as directory creation, chmod/stat/open/truncate/write/close errors, or short write\n- It has a 10 second startup refresh timeout, but refresh timeout/cancel errors are swallowed as refresh failures.\n\nSo CLI startup validation should generally not treat these errors as globally fatal when other LLM auth is configured. From this package’s perspective, the function only affects OpenAI subscription-backed availability; it does not prove that all LLM auth is unusable. A reasonable startup policy is:\n\n- If other configured LLM auth is usable: warn/debug-log the OpenAI subscription refresh/load/save issue and continue.\n- If the selected/required provider depends on this OpenAI subscription and no alternative auth is available: treat absence of usable OpenAI subscription as fatal for that request/startup mode.\n- If the error is a local auth file corruption/permission issue: surface it clearly, but still do not fail unrelated providers."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1779925011,"paths":["internal/subscriptions/openaisub/SPEC.md","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub.go","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub_linux_test.go","internal/subscriptions/openaisub/openaisub_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"a40188aae27f630fe5307723bf762fb64cba06e0","git_merge_base":"1a69a8f846e92dbf07db54d31e21b6e8ca075282"}}